@startuml terminal-module-detail
title "Terminal Module - TUI State & Buffer Components (Single Responsibility)"

!define ACCENTCOLOR #4A90E2
!define SRPCOLOR #E8F8F5
!define EVENTCOLOR #FFE8E8

skinparam style strictuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFACD
skinparam NoteBorderColor #FFD700
skinparam ClassBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam ClassBorderColor ACCENTCOLOR

' Terminal State & Mode
package "Terminal State Management" {
    class TerminalState {
        + output: OutputBuffer
        + input: InputBuffer
        + history: CommandHistory
        + mode: TerminalMode
        --
        + new(): Self
        + add_output(line: String)
        + add_output_lines(lines: Vec<String>)
        + insert_char(c: char)
        + delete_char()
        + move_cursor_left()
        + move_cursor_right()
        + submit_input(): String
        + clear_input()
        + history_previous()
        + history_next()
        + scroll_up()
        + scroll_down()
        + get_mode(): TerminalMode
        --
        **Composition Pattern**:
        Aggregates three SRP-compliant buffer components
        **Single Responsibility**: Orchestrate buffer interactions
    }

    enum TerminalMode {
        Normal            // Waiting for user input
        ExecutingCommand  // Command running
        WaitingLLM        // LLM query in progress
        PromptingInstall  // Installation prompt (M2/M3)
    }

    note right of TerminalState
        **Terminal State Lifecycle**:
        1. Initialize with empty buffers
        2. Poll events → modify state
        3. On Submit: Extract input, add to history
        4. Mode transitions based on input type
        5. UI renders current state
        6. Loop until quit
    end note

    note bottom of TerminalMode
        **Mode Purposes**:
        - Normal: Standard input waiting
        - ExecutingCommand: UI shows spinner/progress
        - WaitingLLM: UI shows waiting message
        - PromptingInstall: (Future) Installation dialog
    end note
}

' SRP-compliant Buffer Components
package "Buffer Components (Single Responsibility Principle)" {
    class OutputBuffer #SRPCOLOR {
        - buffer: Vec<String>
        - scroll_position: usize
        --
        + new(): Self
        + add_line(line: String)
        + add_lines(lines: Vec<String>)
        + lines(&self): &[String]
        + get_visible_lines(height: usize): Vec<&String>
        + scroll_up()
        + scroll_down()
        + scroll_to_bottom()
        + clear()
        - trim_if_needed()
        - auto_scroll_to_bottom()
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Manage scrollable output
        **Max lines**: 10,000 (auto-trim to prevent memory leak)
        **Trim size**: 1,000 lines when limit exceeded
    }

    class InputBuffer #SRPCOLOR {
        - content: String
        - cursor_pos: usize
        --
        + new(): Self
        + insert_char(c: char)
        + delete_char()
        + move_cursor_left()
        + move_cursor_right()
        + content(&self): &str
        + clear()
        - move_cursor_to_start()
        - move_cursor_to_end()
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Manage text input + cursor
        **Unicode support**: Correct grapheme boundary handling
        **Cursor movement**: Grapheme-aware for CJK, emoji

        **NOTE**: Fixed Unicode bug that was causing
        incorrect cursor positioning on multi-byte
        characters. Now uses grapheme_indices
        for proper boundary detection.
    }

    class CommandHistory #SRPCOLOR {
        - history: Vec<String>
        - position: Option<usize>
        --
        + new(): Self
        + add(command: String)
        + previous(): Option<String>
        + next(): Option<String>
        + all(&self): &[String]
        + clear()
        - move_position_backward()
        - move_position_forward()
        --
        **Single Responsibility**: Manage command history navigation
        **Semantics**: Navigate with up/down arrows
        **Position tracking**: Optional index for current position
    }

    note bottom of OutputBuffer
        **Memory Management**:
        - Automatic trimming prevents unbounded growth
        - Keeps recent 9,000 lines when trimmed
        - Scroll position adjusted automatically
        - Prevents memory issues in long sessions
    end note

    note bottom of InputBuffer
        **Grapheme Boundary Handling**:
        Previous bug: Direct char indexing broke on Unicode
        - Multi-byte chars (é, 中) caused wrong position
        - Emoji (👍) off by multiple bytes
        - CJK chars stored as multiple UTF-8 bytes

        Current fix: Uses grapheme_indices()
        - Correct movement on all Unicode
        - Supports emoji properly
        - Handles combining characters
    end note

    note bottom of CommandHistory
        **History Navigation UX**:
        1. User types: "ls -la"
        2. Press Up → shows previous command
        3. Press Up again → shows command before that
        4. Press Down → goes forward in history
        5. Position = None means at current input
    end note
}

' Event System
package "Event Handling" {
    enum TerminalEvent #EVENTCOLOR {
        Quit
        InputChar(char)
        DeleteChar
        MoveCursorLeft
        MoveCursorRight
        HistoryPrevious
        HistoryNext
        ScrollUp
        ScrollDown
        Submit
        TabComplete
        ClearScreen
        Resize(u16, u16)
        Unknown
    }

    class EventHandler {
        + poll_event(timeout: Duration): Result<Option<TerminalEvent>>
        --
        **Responsibilities**:
        - Poll crossterm events with timeout
        - Convert terminal events to TerminalEvent
        - Filter Windows duplicate events (KeyEventKind::Press only)
        - Handle resize events
    }

    note right of EventHandler
        **Keyboard Event Handling**:
        - Uses crossterm for terminal event polling
        - Non-blocking with configurable timeout
        - Filters only Press events on Windows
        (Crossterm generates multiple events per keystroke)
        - Supports arrow keys, Enter, Tab, Ctrl+C
    end note

    note right of TerminalEvent
        **Event Enum Variants**:
        - InputChar(c): Printable character
        - DeleteChar: Backspace
        - MoveCursor*: Arrow keys
        - History*: Up/Down arrows (context-aware)
        - ScrollUp/Down: Page Up/Down
        - Submit: Enter key
        - TabComplete: Tab key
        - ClearScreen: Ctrl+L
        - Resize: Terminal size change
        - Unknown: Unhandled key
    end note
}

' TUI Rendering
package "TUI Rendering" {
    class TerminalUI {
        - terminal: Terminal<CrosstermBackend<Stdout>>
        --
        + new(): Result<Self>
        + render(state: &TerminalState): Result<()>
        - render_output_pane(buf: &mut Buffer, area: Rect, state: &TerminalState)
        - render_input_pane(buf: &mut Buffer, area: Rect, state: &TerminalState)
        - render_status_bar(buf: &mut Buffer, area: Rect, mode: &TerminalMode)
        --
        **Technology**: ratatui (Rust TUI framework)
        **Backend**: Crossterm (terminal control)
        **Layout**: Flex layout system
    }

    note right of TerminalUI
        **Rendering Pipeline**:
        1. Create a new Frame (ratatui)
        2. Layout terminal into 3 areas:
           - Output pane (scrollable)
           - Input pane (single line)
           - Status bar
        3. Render each pane based on state
        4. Draw to terminal backend
        5. Flush output
    end note
}

' Relationships & Composition
TerminalState *-- OutputBuffer
TerminalState *-- InputBuffer
TerminalState *-- CommandHistory
TerminalState --> TerminalMode

TerminalUI --> TerminalState
EventHandler --> TerminalEvent

OutputBuffer --|> "SRP: Scrollable output"
InputBuffer --|> "SRP: Text input + cursor"
CommandHistory --|> "SRP: History navigation"

' Data flow diagram
note top of TerminalState
    **State Composition** (SRP Pattern):
    TerminalState delegates to specialized components:
    - OutputBuffer: Handles output display & scrolling
    - InputBuffer: Handles text input & cursor
    - CommandHistory: Handles history navigation
    Each component has one responsibility
    and can be tested in isolation
end note

note bottom of TerminalUI
    **Rendering Interaction**:
    1. TerminalUI::render() receives &TerminalState
    2. Reads from all buffer components
    3. Constructs ratatui widgets
    4. Manages layout with Flex
    5. Displays cursor position from InputBuffer
    6. Shows visible lines from OutputBuffer
    7. Displays history position indicator
end note

' Performance notes
note right of OutputBuffer
    **Performance Characteristics**:
    - add_line: O(1) append + O(1) trim check
    - trim_if_needed: O(n) slice copy (n = TRIM_LINES)
    - scroll_up/down: O(1) position update
    - get_visible_lines: O(visible_height)
    - Prevents unbounded memory growth
end note

note right of InputBuffer
    **Unicode Performance**:
    - insert_char: O(n) string reallocation
    - delete_char: O(n) string reallocation
    - move_cursor: O(grapheme_count)
    - Tradeoff: Correctness > performance
    (Most inputs <1000 chars, O(n) acceptable)
end note

@enduml
